&lt;p&gt;Critical Care –Registrar (x9 posts)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity for colleagues to join the department of Critical Care within Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust . Imperial led as a hub for the COVID-19 pandemic surge and supported the decompression of other units&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have multiple registrar posts available for 6 month contracts in the first instance with the possibility of extension. We have vacancies across Charing Cross, Hammersmith Hospital and St Mary’s sites and site preference can be discussed further at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charing Cross hospital is a leading specialist centre in Neurosciences including stroke with an acute cerebrovascular thrombectomy service, complex Head and Neck surgery, Urology, Cancer, General Medicine and a busy Emergency Department. The Intensive Care unit on this site has 24 beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hammersmith Hospital provides cardiothoracic and cardiology services, Haem-oncology, Hematology, upper GI and hepatobiliary surgery and is the site of the Queen Charlotte’s Hospital specializing in women’s health and the North West London Renal Centre. The Intensive Care unit on this site has 32 beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Mary’s Hospital a Major Trauma Centre with tertiary and quaternary Vascular Surgery, Acute Abdominal Surgery, Paediatrics General Medicine and a busy emergency department. The Intensive Care unit on this site has 32 beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in research, teaching and quality improvement projects then this is the place to work. This post offers FICE training to those interested in echocardiography and other opportunities as you might expect in a world leading education and research institution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a post open worldwide, be mindful of the GMC requirements and visa requirements from the Home Office. It is mandatory to undertake a language test OET valid for the GMC and Home Office, have your primary medical qualifications verified by ECFMG and a certificate of good standing. If you have previously attempted PLAB, you must let us know at the time of the interview. Face to face and Skype interviews are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non UK / EEA applicants should ensure that they are aware of recent changes to the immigration rules for Postgraduate Doctors and Dentists. For further information on how this may affect your application please contact the Home Office&#39;s Immigration and Nationality Enquiry Bureau on telephone: 0870 606 7766 or by e-mail: indpublicenquiries@ind.homeoffice.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Garnelo Rey, intensive care consultant and vanesa.garnelorey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
